# safqaSeller — Project Structure

## Architecture

Feature-first layout with **MVVM naming** + **Cubit** state management. No standalone domain/use-case layer.

```
lib/
├── core/
│   ├── config/        # AppConfig — base URL, API key, OAuth IDs
│   ├── helper_functions/on_generate_routes.dart  # Named-route switch
│   ├── network/dio_client.dart   # DioHelper (single HTTP client)
│   ├── service_locator.dart      # GetIt registrations
│   ├── storage/                  # CacheHelper (SharedPreferences) + CacheKeys
│   ├── utils/                    # AppColors, TextStyles, AppImages, AppConstants
│   └── widgets/                  # Shared reusable widgets
└── features/<feature>/
    ├── view/
    │   ├── <feature>_view.dart
    │   └── widgets/              # Local widgets (never in core/)
    ├── view_model/
    │   └── <flow>/
    │       ├── <flow>_view_model.dart   # Cubit
    │       └── <flow>_view_model_state.dart
    └── model/
        ├── repositories/<feature>_repository.dart
        └── models/
```

## Feature List

`adaptive_layout`, `auth`, `complete_profile`, `forgot_password`, `home`, `notifications`, `on_boarding`, `profile`, `seller`, `splash`, `subscription`, `terms_and_conditions`, `wallet`

## Adding a New Feature

1. Create folder `lib/features/<name>/` with `view/`, `view_model/`, `model/` sub-folders.
2. Add screen routes to `on_generate_routes.dart` using a string constant `routeName` on the view class.
3. Register repository as `registerLazySingleton` and Cubit as `registerFactory` in `service_locator.dart`.
4. Add route args class to `view/` if the route needs parameters.

## Routing

- All routes live in `lib/core/helper_functions/on_generate_routes.dart` (named-route switch).
- Every screen exposes `static const String routeName = '/my-route';`.
- Pass arguments via `RouteSettings.arguments`; create a typed args class in the feature's `view/` folder.

## Dependency Injection (GetIt)

```dart
// ✅ Repositories → lazySingleton
getIt.registerLazySingleton<MyRepository>(() => MyRepository(getIt()));

// ✅ Cubits → factory (new instance per screen)
getIt.registerFactory<MyCubit>(() => MyCubit(getIt()));

// ✅ App-wide singletons (e.g. AuthViewModel, ProfileViewModel) → registerSingleton
getIt.registerSingleton<AuthViewModel>(AuthViewModel(getIt()));
```

Retrieve with `getIt<T>()`. Never use `context.read` to create a Cubit — always from `getIt`.
